<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="comparisons">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Comparison with congeners.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
There are two other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Sanaa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sanaa" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Sanaa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both reported from the Indomalaya region: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. intermedia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">S. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Beier, 1944, originally reported from Than-Moi, Vietnam, and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. imperialis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">S. imperialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(White, 1846), originally reported from Sylhet, Bangladesh (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
Species File Version 5.0/5.0). The latter species, however, is also recorded from Nepal (
<bibRefCitation author="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="Das Tierreich (Tierreich)" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 468" refId="B3" refString="Beier, M, 1962. Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae I). Das Tierreich (Tierreich) 73: 1 - 468" title="Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae I)." volume="73" year="1962">Beier 1962</bibRefCitation>
). The female of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. regalis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">S. regalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. imperialis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">S. imperialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly in having its ovipositor black at the base, while the ovipositor of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. imperialis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">S. imperialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is yellow (
<bibRefCitation author="Barman, RS" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Fauna of Sikkim, State Fauna Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="193 - 201" refId="B1" refString="Barman, RS, 2003. Insecta: Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae. Zoological Survey of India, Fauna of Sikkim, State Fauna Series 9: 193 - 201" title="Insecta: Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae." volume="9" year="2003">Barman 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Similarly, the ovipositor of S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Sanaa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sanaa intermedia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Sanaa intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is yellow-brown at the base (
<bibRefCitation author="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="Das Tierreich (Tierreich)" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 468" refId="B3" refString="Beier, M, 1962. Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae I). Das Tierreich (Tierreich) 73: 1 - 468" title="Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae I)." volume="73" year="1962">Beier 1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
