<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Habitat and ecology.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
The individual was observed on a rural road near bushes in the mid hills of central Nepal at 15:00 hours (+5.46 GMT) on a clear day. The elevation was 570 m a.sl. Dominant local tree species include 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanopsis indica" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Castanopsis indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(J. Roxb. ex Lindl.) A. DC. and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Schima" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schima wallichii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wallichii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Schima wallichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Korth. along with the bushes of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rubus ellipticus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ellipticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Rubus ellipticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sm.
</paragraph>
